# Keep the Docker build context clean and Linux-correct.
#
# Host node_modules must NEVER be copied into the image: on Windows they contain
# junctions/symlinks into the pnpm store that do not translate to Linux, which
# breaks `pnpm install` and `prisma generate` inside the build. Each image runs
# `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile` to materialize Linux-native dependencies.
**/node_modules

# Build outputs (regenerated inside the image)
**/dist
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/build
**/coverage
**/*.tsbuildinfo
**/.prisma

# Secrets and local env — do not bake into images
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# VCS / tooling / editor noise
.git
.gitignore
.github
.vscode
.idea
**/*.log
npm-debug.log*
pnpm-debug.log*

# Agent / session / graph artifacts
.claude
.graphify
graphify-out

# Container/compose files are not needed inside the image
docker-compose*.yml
Dockerfile
**/Dockerfile
.dockerignore
